1
00:01:51,890 --> 00:01:54,270
辛苦啦
Prime Minister Tony Blair has led political

2
00:01:54,290 --> 00:01:56,070
辛苦啦
tributes from a grateful nation...

3
00:01:56,090 --> 00:01:57,630
辛苦啦
Hey, Dad.

4
00:01:57,650 --> 00:02:00,980
辛苦啦
- Morning, sunshine. You up? - Up? I'm out and about!

5
00:02:01,570 --> 00:02:04,330
辛苦啦
Hm, pardon me, early riser.

6
00:02:04,370 --> 00:02:05,850
辛苦啦
What is it, Dad?

7
00:02:05,890 --> 00:02:07,910
辛苦啦
You said there was a match today.

8
00:02:07,930 --> 00:02:10,150
辛苦啦
Oh, yeah. Only a crappy school thing.

9
00:02:10,170 --> 00:02:11,910
辛苦啦
Oh, well, I wanna come. Where is it?

10
00:02:11,930 --> 00:02:14,350
辛苦啦
No, Dad, seriously, it's not that type of match.

11
00:02:14,370 --> 00:02:16,490
辛苦啦
No parents are gonna be there.

12
00:02:16,530 --> 00:02:18,400
辛苦啦
You're wrong. I'll be there.

13
00:02:23,410 --> 00:02:25,590
辛苦啦
The Queen's 80th birthday celebrations.

14
00:02:25,610 --> 00:02:28,550
辛苦啦
Her sense of duty and service, said Mr Blair...

15
00:02:31,770 --> 00:02:33,090
辛苦啦
We set?

16
00:02:38,210 --> 00:02:39,730
辛苦啦
Boss.

17
00:02:39,770 --> 00:02:41,130
辛苦啦
Morning.

18
00:02:41,170 --> 00:02:42,290
辛苦啦
Steve.

19
00:02:42,330 --> 00:02:44,110
辛苦啦
How's the report coming? ACPO are asking.

20
00:02:44,130 --> 00:02:46,110
辛苦啦
Yeah, should be with you by the end of play today.

21
00:02:46,130 --> 00:02:47,470
辛苦啦
Any nasty surprises?

22
00:02:47,490 --> 00:02:50,550
辛苦啦
I wish. It's gonna be a job for me to find something to do.

23
00:02:50,570 --> 00:02:52,500
辛苦啦
I have a hunch you'll manage.

24
00:02:55,210 --> 00:02:56,710
辛苦啦
What's with the TV crew, Dave?

25
00:02:56,730 --> 00:02:58,850
辛苦啦
Old news.

26
00:04:21,370 --> 00:04:23,290
辛苦啦
Hey. What's up?

27
00:04:23,330 --> 00:04:25,950
辛苦啦
So, er, Jack just texted to say you're picking him up

28
00:04:25,970 --> 00:04:27,070
辛苦啦
from the match.

29
00:04:27,090 --> 00:04:29,410
辛苦啦
Yeah. Is there a problem?

30
00:04:29,450 --> 00:04:32,650
辛苦啦
Well, back a month and you're running the show.

31
00:04:32,690 --> 00:04:34,010
辛苦啦
Look, just...

32
00:04:34,050 --> 00:04:35,630
辛苦啦
just make sure you're there.

33
00:04:35,650 --> 00:04:38,450
辛苦啦
Fran, I'll be there.

34
00:04:43,170 --> 00:04:44,490
辛苦啦
Go on, Jack.

35
00:04:55,130 --> 00:04:58,550
辛苦啦
So, I was thinking, we could have a mid-week boys' night in.

36
00:04:58,570 --> 00:05:01,970
辛苦啦
Take-away, DVD?

37
00:05:02,010 --> 00:05:03,550
辛苦啦
I've cleared it with Mum.

38
00:05:03,570 --> 00:05:06,250
辛苦啦
I said I'd stay over at Ryan's.

39
00:05:06,290 --> 00:05:08,820
辛苦啦
Can't you stay at Ryan's another night?

40
00:05:12,290 --> 00:05:15,110
辛苦啦
I was thinking, how about you spend one week with me,

41
00:05:15,130 --> 00:05:16,310
辛苦啦
one week with your mum...?

42
00:05:16,330 --> 00:05:19,570
辛苦啦
You know, that gives Mum and Mike some space, too.

43
00:05:19,610 --> 00:05:21,230
辛苦啦
Did Mum ask you to do this?

44
00:05:21,250 --> 00:05:22,490
辛苦啦
No!

45
00:05:22,530 --> 00:05:24,930
辛苦啦
But she's fine about it, if you are.

46
00:05:27,330 --> 00:05:29,010
辛苦啦
Can I think about it?

47
00:05:30,970 --> 00:05:33,370
辛苦啦
Absolutely. Yeah.

48
00:05:33,410 --> 00:05:37,090
辛苦啦
Look, go and stay at Ryan's tonight and we'll chat.

49
00:05:37,130 --> 00:05:38,530
辛苦啦
Come here.

50
00:06:00,810 --> 00:06:03,150
辛苦啦
With so many recent successes nationwide

51
00:06:03,170 --> 00:06:07,490
辛苦啦
where DNA has played a key role in solving cold cases,

52
00:06:07,530 --> 00:06:09,670
辛苦啦
attention will inevitably turn to

53
00:06:09,690 --> 00:06:13,730
辛苦啦
unsolved murders in Wales, most notably the double murders

54
00:06:13,770 --> 00:06:16,270
辛苦啦
of Peter and Gwenda Dixon in Pembrokeshire.

55
00:06:16,290 --> 00:06:17,670
辛苦啦
Jonathan Hill reports.

56
00:06:17,690 --> 00:06:20,870
辛苦啦
Over 17 years ago, the couple were blasted to death

57
00:06:20,890 --> 00:06:24,810
辛苦啦
with a shotgun by an unknown killer as they walked along here

58
00:06:24,850 --> 00:06:28,410
辛苦啦
at the Coastal Path in Little Haven in Pembrokeshire.

59
00:06:28,450 --> 00:06:30,350
辛苦啦
Despite a huge police investigation,

60
00:06:30,370 --> 00:06:32,150
辛苦啦
no-one was ever charged for the crime,

61
00:06:32,170 --> 00:06:35,770
辛苦啦
and the Dixon family's long wait for justice continues.

62
00:06:35,810 --> 00:06:38,110
辛苦啦
A lot of people have said they no longer feel comfortable

63
00:06:38,130 --> 00:06:40,060
辛苦啦
coming to this path any more.

64
00:06:40,650 --> 00:06:43,050
辛苦啦
They say it no longer feels the same.

65
00:06:44,930 --> 00:06:46,910
辛苦啦
We asked Dyfed Powys Police for a comment

66
00:06:46,930 --> 00:06:48,870
辛苦啦
but were told that no-one was available.

67
00:06:48,890 --> 00:06:51,290
辛苦啦
Old news?

68
00:06:51,330 --> 00:06:55,070
辛苦啦
Meanwhile, the identity of John and Gwenda Dixon's vicious killer

69
00:06:55,090 --> 00:06:56,450
辛苦啦
remains unknown.

70
00:07:03,490 --> 00:07:05,290
辛苦啦
How you settling in, Steve?

71
00:07:06,250 --> 00:07:07,930
辛苦啦
It's like I never left.

72
00:07:08,330 --> 00:07:10,670
辛苦啦
I found only one area where we're exposed.

73
00:07:10,690 --> 00:07:13,270
辛苦啦
No thorough forensic reviews of serious crimes.

74
00:07:13,290 --> 00:07:15,170
辛苦啦
Most notably Coastal Path.

75
00:07:16,610 --> 00:07:17,970
辛苦啦
You saw the news.

76
00:07:19,530 --> 00:07:22,050
辛苦啦
Yeah. What's the story?

77
00:07:25,770 --> 00:07:29,170
辛苦啦
The unlikelihood of finding anything new.

78
00:07:29,210 --> 00:07:31,510
辛苦啦
The distress that would cause the Dixon family.

79
00:07:31,530 --> 00:07:34,390
辛苦啦
And, if we failed, the delight the media would take

80
00:07:34,410 --> 00:07:36,270
辛苦啦
in hauling us through the muck.

81
00:07:36,290 --> 00:07:38,990
辛苦啦
A few years back, they branded us "institutionally incompetent",

82
00:07:39,010 --> 00:07:40,050
辛苦啦
and it stuck.

83
00:07:42,250 --> 00:07:45,770
辛苦啦
Well, it's about time we did something about that.

84
00:07:45,810 --> 00:07:48,670
辛苦啦
I'd like to take a look at Coastal Path, see if there's anything there.

85
00:07:48,690 --> 00:07:50,130
辛苦啦
That OK with you?

86
00:07:50,170 --> 00:07:52,100
辛苦啦
You don't need my permission.

87
00:07:52,610 --> 00:07:56,210
辛苦啦
DCI George Jones was SIO on it. Is he still about?

88
00:07:56,250 --> 00:08:00,090
辛苦啦
Yeah, he is. But, Steve, go easy on the old bloke.

89
00:08:21,650 --> 00:08:23,550
辛苦啦
Thank you for seeing me, sir.

90
00:08:23,570 --> 00:08:24,790
辛苦啦
A police dog found them.

91
00:08:24,810 --> 00:08:27,170
辛苦啦
Six days after they were reported missing.

92
00:08:29,010 --> 00:08:31,480
辛苦啦
The maggots gave us the time of death.

93
00:08:32,490 --> 00:08:36,460
辛苦啦
After he murdered them, the attacker stole Peter Dixon's wallet

94
00:08:36,490 --> 00:08:38,410
辛苦啦
and wedding ring.

95
00:08:38,450 --> 00:08:40,830
辛苦啦
It's not much of a reason to end two lives, is it?

96
00:08:40,850 --> 00:08:43,110
辛苦啦
Gwenda Dixon was sexually assaulted

97
00:08:43,130 --> 00:08:45,950
辛苦啦
with her husband lying dead not six feet away.

98
00:08:45,970 --> 00:08:47,950
辛苦啦
He was a sick, sadistic bastard.

99
00:08:47,970 --> 00:08:49,770
辛苦啦
He didn't need a reason.

100
00:08:53,210 --> 00:08:54,890
辛苦啦
We did the best we could.

101
00:09:00,170 --> 00:09:02,040
辛苦啦
I won't be made a scapegoat.

102
00:09:03,250 --> 00:09:05,180
辛苦啦
That's not why I'm here, sir.

103
00:09:09,490 --> 00:09:12,070
辛苦啦
So, four days after the murders, a man walked into

104
00:09:12,090 --> 00:09:16,410
辛苦啦
Pembroke Bespoke Jewellers and sold a 22-carat gold band.

105
00:09:16,450 --> 00:09:20,270
辛苦啦
The band matched the description of Peter Dixon's stolen wedding ring.

106
00:09:20,290 --> 00:09:23,150
辛苦啦
And the seller of the ring had signed the receipt J Cooper.

107
00:09:23,170 --> 00:09:26,010
辛苦啦
Now, on the basis of this information,

108
00:09:26,050 --> 00:09:28,490
辛苦啦
one of your team, a DC Dylan Rees?

109
00:09:29,850 --> 00:09:34,850
辛苦啦
He questioned a John William Cooper of 28 Rose Meadow Lane, Birchmede.

110
00:09:36,250 --> 00:09:37,710
辛苦啦
Cooper said that the ring was his own

111
00:09:37,730 --> 00:09:39,550
辛苦啦
and that he sold it because he needed the cash,

112
00:09:39,570 --> 00:09:41,830
辛苦啦
and then his wife confirmed the story.

113
00:09:41,850 --> 00:09:44,250
辛苦啦
And then no further action was taken.

114
00:09:45,570 --> 00:09:48,770
辛苦啦
I'm curious to hear your view on this.

115
00:09:48,810 --> 00:09:51,490
辛苦啦
I sent a DC to do a DCI's job.

116
00:09:51,530 --> 00:09:54,490
辛苦啦
I should've questioned Cooper myself, but we...

117
00:09:54,530 --> 00:09:55,970
辛苦啦
we were swamped.

118
00:09:57,010 --> 00:09:59,830
辛苦啦
After the case was closed, I learnt that Rees

119
00:09:59,850 --> 00:10:02,610
辛苦啦
drank in the same pub as Cooper, together.

120
00:10:03,610 --> 00:10:06,250
辛苦啦
My view is that Cooper...

121
00:10:06,290 --> 00:10:09,050
辛苦啦
used the fact they knew each other.

122
00:10:09,090 --> 00:10:10,650
辛苦啦
That Rees...

123
00:10:10,690 --> 00:10:12,130
辛苦啦
was manipulated.

124
00:10:14,370 --> 00:10:16,900
辛苦啦
- Where's Cooper now? - Dyffryn Prison.

125
00:10:16,930 --> 00:10:20,640
辛苦啦
He was sentenced to 16 years in 1998 for a string of, er...

126
00:10:21,210 --> 00:10:22,790
辛苦啦
burglaries and robberies.

127
00:10:22,810 --> 00:10:26,050
辛苦啦
The investigation was codenamed Huntsman.

128
00:10:26,090 --> 00:10:29,370
辛苦啦
They interviewed Cooper, but didn't get anything.

129
00:10:29,410 --> 00:10:33,450
辛苦啦
16 years in 1998...

130
00:10:33,490 --> 00:10:36,500
辛苦啦
If he's behaved himself, he'll be up for parole.

131
00:10:41,370 --> 00:10:44,710
辛苦啦
Where it happened is just below Talbenny church.

132
00:10:44,730 --> 00:10:47,610
辛苦啦
The spot is marked by a plaque.

133
00:10:49,370 --> 00:10:52,830
辛苦啦
The Dixons' son and daughter leave a wreath every year.

134
00:11:58,490 --> 00:12:00,250
辛苦啦
You found us, then.

135
00:12:01,610 --> 00:12:04,230
辛苦啦
So, you're doing a bit of digging on John William Cooper?

136
00:12:04,250 --> 00:12:05,770
辛苦啦
I am.

137
00:12:05,810 --> 00:12:08,680
辛苦啦
Let's hope you have better luck than we did.

138
00:12:14,210 --> 00:12:16,890
辛苦啦
Operation Huntsman.

139
00:12:16,930 --> 00:12:18,370
辛苦啦
This was us.

140
00:12:18,410 --> 00:12:20,670
辛苦啦
There's a few odds and sods stored elsewhere,

141
00:12:20,690 --> 00:12:24,370
辛苦啦
but most of this was confiscated from Cooper's home.

142
00:12:24,410 --> 00:12:26,090
辛苦啦
The place was a pigsty.

143
00:12:27,970 --> 00:12:31,230
辛苦啦
You arrested him for a string of burglaries and robberies,

144
00:12:31,250 --> 00:12:34,310
辛苦啦
but you also questioned him about the murders at Coastal Path.

145
00:12:34,330 --> 00:12:36,490
辛苦啦
- Why? - His MO, sir.

146
00:12:36,530 --> 00:12:39,670
辛苦啦
We did him for a robbery that was a carbon copy of the Coastal Path.

147
00:12:39,690 --> 00:12:42,050
辛苦啦
Robbery, tied-up victim, a shotgun.

148
00:12:42,090 --> 00:12:45,550
辛苦啦
That's why we also questioned him about Scoveston Park.

149
00:12:46,730 --> 00:12:48,550
辛苦啦
20 years ago, Scoveston Park?

150
00:12:48,570 --> 00:12:51,090
辛苦啦
21 years ago now. December, '85.

151
00:12:52,210 --> 00:12:54,970
辛苦啦
Theft, arson and double murder.

152
00:12:57,130 --> 00:13:00,200
辛苦啦
- Brother and sister. - Richard and Helen Thomas.

153
00:13:01,090 --> 00:13:03,870
辛苦啦
The difference was that the killer resorted to arson

154
00:13:03,890 --> 00:13:06,420
辛苦啦
to cover his tracks. He started a fire.

155
00:13:07,210 --> 00:13:09,690
辛苦啦
He completely destroyed the place.

156
00:13:09,730 --> 00:13:11,550
辛苦啦
Tough on evidence gathering.

157
00:13:11,570 --> 00:13:13,900
辛苦啦
Yeah. And even tougher on forensics.

158
00:13:15,410 --> 00:13:17,590
辛苦啦
Did Cooper tell you anything in the interviews?

159
00:13:17,610 --> 00:13:20,270
辛苦啦
Nothing. When we mentioned the murders, he just shut down.

160
00:13:20,290 --> 00:13:22,130
辛苦啦
We had to move on.

161
00:13:22,170 --> 00:13:23,470
辛苦啦
With all the lesser offences,

162
00:13:23,490 --> 00:13:26,930
辛苦啦
we found almost every single stolen item in his home.

163
00:13:26,970 --> 00:13:29,570
辛苦啦
You charge them with what you can prove.

164
00:13:30,690 --> 00:13:32,550
辛苦啦
- Did you speak to the family? - We did.

165
00:13:32,570 --> 00:13:34,390
辛苦啦
Yeah, the wife gave us nothing.

166
00:13:34,410 --> 00:13:36,630
辛苦啦
She was more frightened of him than us.

167
00:13:36,650 --> 00:13:38,570
辛苦啦
The son was useful.

168
00:13:38,610 --> 00:13:40,310
辛苦啦
Yeah, he hated his dad, though.

169
00:13:40,330 --> 00:13:42,530
辛苦啦
He wanted nothing to do with him.

170
00:13:44,010 --> 00:13:46,990
辛苦啦
The reason your Disability Allowance payment has been delayed

171
00:13:47,010 --> 00:13:48,830
辛苦啦
is because you changed your first name.

172
00:13:48,850 --> 00:13:51,270
辛苦啦
Yeah, eight years ago, by statutory declaration.

173
00:13:51,290 --> 00:13:53,670
辛苦啦
I gave you people a copy of the certificate!

174
00:13:53,690 --> 00:13:55,090
辛苦啦
Look...

175
00:13:55,130 --> 00:13:56,510
辛苦啦
I've had enough of this.

176
00:13:56,530 --> 00:13:58,390
辛苦啦
Can you get a manager on the line, please?

177
00:13:58,410 --> 00:14:01,010
辛苦啦
I'm not authorised to do that, sir.

178
00:14:01,050 --> 00:14:03,470
辛苦啦
- What's your first name, Mr Cooper? - Andrew.

179
00:14:03,490 --> 00:14:05,410
辛苦啦
Not Adrian, Andrew.

180
00:14:05,450 --> 00:14:07,090
辛苦啦
Andrew Cooper.

181
00:14:07,130 --> 00:14:08,210
辛苦啦
And...

182
00:14:08,250 --> 00:14:10,150
辛苦啦
don't talk to me like I'm an idiot.

183
00:14:10,170 --> 00:14:13,240
辛苦啦
- Hold the line, please, sir. - No, please don't...

184
00:14:13,410 --> 00:14:17,570
辛苦啦
Please continue to hold. Your call is important to us.

185
00:14:31,840 --> 00:14:33,840
辛苦啦
- Hi, Dad. - Oh, hello!

186
00:14:35,440 --> 00:14:36,480
辛苦啦
Laundry.

187
00:14:36,520 --> 00:14:40,340
辛苦啦
The machine at the salon's on the blink and you're closer than Mum's.

188
00:14:40,360 --> 00:14:41,680
辛苦啦
Well...

189
00:14:42,880 --> 00:14:45,550
辛苦啦
good to know I'm useful for something.

190
00:15:09,880 --> 00:15:11,240
辛苦啦
Payment.

191
00:15:13,400 --> 00:15:15,280
辛苦啦
"Maximum hold."

192
00:15:15,320 --> 00:15:17,080
辛苦啦
Thank you, love.

193
00:15:17,120 --> 00:15:19,240
辛苦啦
The place is looking nice now.

194
00:15:19,280 --> 00:15:20,640
辛苦啦
Very tidy.

195
00:15:20,680 --> 00:15:24,060
辛苦啦
It'll do, until I find something a bit more permanent.

196
00:15:24,080 --> 00:15:27,040
辛苦啦
Do you want to stay, have a bite to eat?

197
00:15:27,080 --> 00:15:28,240
辛苦啦
Sorry.

198
00:15:28,280 --> 00:15:29,700
辛苦啦
Late for the cinema.

199
00:15:29,720 --> 00:15:31,400
辛苦啦
OK, love, enjoy yourself.

200
00:15:36,240 --> 00:15:38,620
辛苦啦
Jack's really chuffed that you're back.

201
00:15:38,640 --> 00:15:40,000
辛苦啦
Is he?

202
00:15:40,040 --> 00:15:41,800
辛苦啦
Don't try too hard.

203
00:15:42,840 --> 00:15:44,720
辛苦啦
Just give him a bit of time.

204
00:15:45,760 --> 00:15:47,880
辛苦啦
Right, OK.

205
00:15:47,920 --> 00:15:50,050
辛苦啦
I'll pick up the stuff tomorrow.

206
00:15:50,080 --> 00:15:51,120
辛苦啦
Hey...

207
00:15:52,240 --> 00:15:54,020
辛苦啦
When did you become so mature?

208
00:15:54,040 --> 00:15:56,480
辛苦啦
Ages ago.

209
00:15:56,520 --> 00:15:58,160
辛苦啦
I'm a girl.

210
00:16:25,320 --> 00:16:27,840
辛苦啦
John William Cooper. Do you know him?

211
00:16:27,880 --> 00:16:31,180
辛苦啦
Yeah, I've heard of him. And Operation Huntsman, obviously.

212
00:16:31,200 --> 00:16:34,020
辛苦啦
What would you say if I told you his offending kit for the robberies

213
00:16:34,040 --> 00:16:36,420
辛苦啦
was black gloves, balaclava and shotgun?

214
00:16:36,440 --> 00:16:38,360
辛苦啦
I'd say Nolton Hill Estate.

215
00:16:41,720 --> 00:16:43,180
辛苦啦
The shotgun he used,

216
00:16:43,200 --> 00:16:46,660
辛苦啦
recovered from a robbery gone wrong in the village of Sardis.

217
00:16:46,680 --> 00:16:49,460
辛苦啦
It was the customised shoulder strap which got my attention.

218
00:16:49,480 --> 00:16:51,160
辛苦啦
Sawn-off, modified stock.

219
00:16:52,240 --> 00:16:53,500
辛苦啦
Jesus, Steve, is it him?

220
00:16:53,520 --> 00:16:55,240
辛苦啦
Him who?

221
00:16:55,280 --> 00:16:56,960
辛苦啦
What's going on?

222
00:16:57,000 --> 00:16:59,000
辛苦啦
Do you remember Nolton Hill?

223
00:17:00,200 --> 00:17:02,580
辛苦啦
Ten years ago. A few months before I left.

224
00:17:02,600 --> 00:17:05,300
辛苦啦
A masked man with a shotgun attacked five teenagers

225
00:17:05,320 --> 00:17:06,580
辛苦啦
near the Nolton Hill Estate.

226
00:17:06,600 --> 00:17:09,380
辛苦啦
One of the girls was raped. Another sexually assaulted.

227
00:17:09,400 --> 00:17:11,580
辛苦啦
- It was never solved. - I remember.

228
00:17:11,600 --> 00:17:13,580
辛苦啦
DI Richards and myself were called in to assist.

229
00:17:13,600 --> 00:17:15,840
辛苦啦
The two boys knew about guns.

230
00:17:15,880 --> 00:17:17,500
辛苦啦
Yeah, they used to do a bit of rabbiting.

231
00:17:17,520 --> 00:17:20,820
辛苦啦
Their description of the shotgun that the attacker used

232
00:17:20,840 --> 00:17:22,260
辛苦啦
exactly matched that gun.

233
00:17:22,280 --> 00:17:24,280
辛苦啦
Hang on. Back up a bit, Steve.

234
00:17:24,320 --> 00:17:26,500
辛苦啦
The last I heard, you were looking at Coastal Path.

235
00:17:26,520 --> 00:17:27,840
辛苦啦
I was.

236
00:17:27,880 --> 00:17:29,080
辛苦啦
I am.

237
00:17:30,360 --> 00:17:32,040
辛苦啦
And that led me to this.

238
00:17:34,000 --> 00:17:36,120
辛苦啦
I'll ask you again, John,

239
00:17:36,160 --> 00:17:38,860
辛苦啦
regarding the murders of Peter and Gwenda Dixon

240
00:17:38,880 --> 00:17:42,440
辛苦啦
on the morning of Thursday 29th June, 1989,

241
00:17:42,480 --> 00:17:44,610
辛苦啦
were you the person responsible?

242
00:17:45,160 --> 00:17:47,680
辛苦啦
I am not a murderer.

243
00:17:47,720 --> 00:17:49,900
辛苦啦
- Strong accent. - South Pembrokeshire.

244
00:17:49,920 --> 00:17:51,160
辛苦啦
Watch this...

245
00:17:51,200 --> 00:17:53,720
辛苦啦
John, what about Scoveston Park?

246
00:17:53,760 --> 00:17:56,820
辛苦啦
We have witnesses who say that you knew Richard and Helen Thomas.

247
00:17:56,840 --> 00:17:59,260
辛苦啦
My client is exercising his right to silence.

248
00:17:59,280 --> 00:18:02,010
辛苦啦
John... Come on, John, don't be like that.

249
00:18:03,480 --> 00:18:04,520
辛苦啦
John.

250
00:18:04,560 --> 00:18:05,680
辛苦啦
John!

251
00:18:06,800 --> 00:18:08,280
辛苦啦
Steve...

252
00:18:08,320 --> 00:18:10,980
辛苦啦
ever since Huntsman, gossip has put Cooper in the frame

253
00:18:11,000 --> 00:18:13,420
辛苦啦
- for 101 offences. - I'm talking about just three.

254
00:18:13,440 --> 00:18:17,120
辛苦啦
Coastal Path, Scoveston Park, Nolton Hill.

255
00:18:19,520 --> 00:18:21,640
辛苦啦
I think he did them all.

256
00:18:54,520 --> 00:18:56,400
辛苦啦
Not now, Jack.

257
00:19:02,520 --> 00:19:03,800
辛苦啦
Here they come.

258
00:19:06,560 --> 00:19:09,180
辛苦啦
How did Operation Huntsman miss all this?

259
00:19:09,200 --> 00:19:10,380
辛苦啦
They didn't, ma'am.

260
00:19:10,400 --> 00:19:12,580
辛苦啦
They questioned Cooper on all three cases

261
00:19:12,600 --> 00:19:14,400
辛苦啦
and he just stayed mute.

262
00:19:14,440 --> 00:19:18,090
辛苦啦
Plus, as I touched on earlier, there was no hard evidence.

263
00:19:18,960 --> 00:19:20,820
辛苦啦
Where's your hard evidence, Steve?

264
00:19:20,840 --> 00:19:23,600
辛苦啦
It's waiting for us to find, ma'am.

265
00:19:23,640 --> 00:19:26,220
辛苦啦
Thanks to Huntsman and the original investigations,

266
00:19:26,240 --> 00:19:29,560
辛苦啦
we have access to over 3,000 exhibits in storage.

267
00:19:29,600 --> 00:19:33,260
辛苦啦
That's a potential treasure trove of victim and perpetrator DNA.

268
00:19:33,280 --> 00:19:34,660
辛苦啦
At the time of Huntsman,

269
00:19:34,680 --> 00:19:37,220
辛苦啦
the science wasn't up to scratch on age-degraded trace DNA.

270
00:19:37,240 --> 00:19:40,380
辛苦啦
But as we know, things have come a long way since.

271
00:19:41,040 --> 00:19:42,780
辛苦啦
Say you get enough to charge him.

272
00:19:42,800 --> 00:19:46,460
辛苦啦
Charging a man with the murders of four adults is clear, simple.

273
00:19:46,480 --> 00:19:49,880
辛苦啦
But you add five minors, rape, sexual assault,

274
00:19:49,920 --> 00:19:51,940
辛苦啦
the Crown's case could seem muddled.

275
00:19:51,960 --> 00:19:54,280
辛苦啦
The CPS won't like that.

276
00:19:54,320 --> 00:19:57,500
辛苦啦
Perhaps it would be wiser to confine the review to the two murders.

277
00:19:57,520 --> 00:20:01,720
辛苦啦
With respect, ma'am, I interviewed the five victims as a WDC.

278
00:20:01,760 --> 00:20:04,760
辛苦啦
And it made quite an impression on me.

279
00:20:04,800 --> 00:20:07,220
辛苦啦
So much so, I've kept tabs on them over the years.

280
00:20:07,240 --> 00:20:09,580
辛苦啦
Now, some are doing better than others, but...

281
00:20:09,600 --> 00:20:12,280
辛苦啦
all of them have been scarred for life.

282
00:20:12,320 --> 00:20:14,660
辛苦啦
They had their childhood stolen from them that night.

283
00:20:14,680 --> 00:20:17,680
辛苦啦
They deserve another chance at justice.

284
00:20:17,720 --> 00:20:19,980
辛苦啦
As do all the victims and their families.

285
00:20:20,000 --> 00:20:22,020
辛苦啦
All I'm saying is, if you try to prove too much,

286
00:20:22,040 --> 00:20:24,200
辛苦啦
you could lose everything.

287
00:20:24,240 --> 00:20:28,500
辛苦啦
The killings at Scoveston Park and Coastal Path are like two bricks.

288
00:20:28,520 --> 00:20:32,100
辛苦啦
And the attacks on the kids is the mortar that holds them together.

289
00:20:32,120 --> 00:20:34,640
辛苦啦
It has elements of both cases.

290
00:20:34,680 --> 00:20:36,560
辛苦啦
And, ma'am, erm...

291
00:20:36,600 --> 00:20:38,060
辛苦啦
what are the odds that offences,

292
00:20:38,080 --> 00:20:41,120
辛苦啦
which share so much similar fact evidence,

293
00:20:41,160 --> 00:20:44,810
辛苦啦
in such a small area, were committed by more than one man?

294
00:20:47,760 --> 00:20:51,180
辛苦啦
You know, if we reinvestigate and it doesn't go our way,

295
00:20:51,200 --> 00:20:55,560
辛苦啦
the media, the public, the families, they'll crucify us.

296
00:20:55,600 --> 00:20:58,610
辛苦啦
And if we don't go ahead, it could be far worse.

297
00:20:58,880 --> 00:21:00,220
辛苦啦
We've put a call into MAPPA.

298
00:21:00,240 --> 00:21:02,540
辛苦啦
A date's been set for his parole hearing.

299
00:21:02,560 --> 00:21:04,260
辛苦啦
He could be out in three months.

300
00:21:04,280 --> 00:21:06,400
辛苦啦
If he did do these murders,

301
00:21:06,440 --> 00:21:08,910
辛苦啦
he is, by definition, a serial killer.

302
00:21:09,720 --> 00:21:13,440
辛苦啦
And given the opportunity, men like him...

303
00:21:13,480 --> 00:21:15,160
辛苦啦
they always kill again.

304
00:21:28,400 --> 00:21:29,800
辛苦啦
Next.

305
00:21:54,320 --> 00:21:57,640
辛苦啦
The next time you visit, make an effort, will you?

306
00:21:59,720 --> 00:22:02,120
辛苦啦
You look like an old woman.

307
00:22:02,160 --> 00:22:03,960
辛苦啦
Adrian's back.

308
00:22:04,000 --> 00:22:05,200
辛苦啦
What?

309
00:22:05,240 --> 00:22:07,060
辛苦啦
I saw Shirley from Birchmede.

310
00:22:07,080 --> 00:22:09,940
辛苦啦
Her daughter's a receptionist in the hospital.

311
00:22:09,960 --> 00:22:12,340
辛苦啦
Apparently, he was walking with a stick.

312
00:22:12,360 --> 00:22:13,680
辛苦啦
A stick?

313
00:22:13,720 --> 00:22:16,260
辛苦啦
- Well, that's gotta be a scam. - Well, that's what she said.

314
00:22:16,280 --> 00:22:18,260
辛苦啦
Anyway, Adrian wasn't like that.

315
00:22:18,280 --> 00:22:19,640
辛苦啦
He was a worker.

316
00:22:19,680 --> 00:22:21,540
辛苦啦
What, you're defending him now, are you, hm?

317
00:22:21,560 --> 00:22:23,840
辛苦啦
He's dead to us.

318
00:22:38,400 --> 00:22:41,000
辛苦啦
Sorry, Andrew. Did I hurt you?

319
00:22:41,040 --> 00:22:42,800
辛苦啦
It wasn't you.

320
00:22:43,960 --> 00:22:46,560
辛苦啦
It's all right, just relax, I've got you.

321
00:23:18,040 --> 00:23:20,160
辛苦啦
28 Rose Meadow Lane.

322
00:23:20,200 --> 00:23:22,870
辛苦啦
Cooper's last home before he went inside.

323
00:23:23,880 --> 00:23:26,140
辛苦啦
Walk in any direction from this point

324
00:23:26,160 --> 00:23:29,460
辛苦啦
and you'll hit a home he targeted between '83 and '96.

325
00:23:29,480 --> 00:23:31,140
辛苦啦
It's the hub of the wheel.

326
00:23:31,160 --> 00:23:32,840
辛苦啦
In this tiny area,

327
00:23:32,880 --> 00:23:36,360
辛苦啦
34 burglaries and robberies, one rape of a minor,

328
00:23:36,400 --> 00:23:38,670
辛苦啦
one indecent assault of a minor...

329
00:23:39,240 --> 00:23:40,760
辛苦啦
and two murders.

330
00:23:43,280 --> 00:23:44,880
辛苦啦
If walls could talk.

331
00:23:52,000 --> 00:23:53,720
辛苦啦
Been back since?

332
00:23:53,760 --> 00:23:56,560
辛苦啦
A few times to see how the kids were doing.

333
00:24:01,600 --> 00:24:04,980
辛苦啦
So, I was thinking a start-up team of six, including us,

334
00:24:05,000 --> 00:24:06,260
辛苦啦
cherry-picked from division.

335
00:24:06,280 --> 00:24:09,040
辛苦啦
That way, we can keep things covert

336
00:24:09,080 --> 00:24:10,660
辛苦啦
and it should be easier on our budget.

337
00:24:10,680 --> 00:24:12,440
辛苦啦
Mm, sounds like a plan.

338
00:24:13,760 --> 00:24:16,020
辛苦啦
I really appreciate you bringing me in on this, Steve.

339
00:24:16,040 --> 00:24:18,560
辛苦啦
Your reputation brought you in.

340
00:24:18,600 --> 00:24:21,040
辛苦啦
WDC to DI in ten years.

341
00:24:21,080 --> 00:24:23,080
辛苦啦
Says Mr DS to Superintendent.

342
00:24:23,120 --> 00:24:24,560
辛苦啦
London.

343
00:24:24,600 --> 00:24:26,400
辛苦啦
The worst years of my life.

344
00:24:29,600 --> 00:24:32,860
辛苦啦
Yeah, I was sorry to hear about you and your missus.

345
00:24:33,120 --> 00:24:34,800
辛苦啦
It is what it is.

346
00:24:51,640 --> 00:24:54,710
辛苦啦
They were so close to home when he attacked them.

347
00:24:55,560 --> 00:24:57,440
辛苦啦
It looks so bloody ordinary.

348
00:25:01,960 --> 00:25:04,080
辛苦啦
To Operation Ottawa.

349
00:25:07,520 --> 00:25:09,120
辛苦啦
To Operation Ottawa.

350
00:26:11,410 --> 00:26:12,610
辛苦啦
It's all right.

351
00:26:13,840 --> 00:26:15,800
辛苦啦
This is home.

352
00:26:15,840 --> 00:26:17,700
辛苦啦
The first rule of Operation Ottawa

353
00:26:17,730 --> 00:26:20,420
辛苦啦
is you do not talk about Operation Ottawa.

354
00:26:20,450 --> 00:26:22,620
辛苦啦
The second rule of Operation Ottawa is...?

355
00:26:22,650 --> 00:26:25,180
辛苦啦
You do not talk about Operation Ottawa.

356
00:26:25,450 --> 00:26:27,730
辛苦啦
It's from Fight Club. It's a film.

357
00:26:27,760 --> 00:26:30,600
辛苦啦
Thank you, Barry Norman.

358
00:26:30,650 --> 00:26:35,000
辛苦啦
We don't say a word to friends, colleagues or family.

359
00:26:35,040 --> 00:26:37,500
辛苦啦
Yeah, they'll get narky with us, but it's the way it has to be.

360
00:26:37,530 --> 00:26:40,540
辛苦啦
We don't want Cooper, or the media, seeing us coming.

361
00:26:40,560 --> 00:26:42,040
辛苦啦
Boss...

362
00:26:42,080 --> 00:26:44,800
辛苦啦
Cold cases are 99% forensics.

363
00:26:44,840 --> 00:26:47,180
辛苦啦
So, we need to do everything we can

364
00:26:47,210 --> 00:26:51,410
辛苦啦
to help the scientists find that DNA golden nugget,

365
00:26:51,450 --> 00:26:56,170
辛苦啦
the DNA hit that unites culprit and victim in the same time and place.

366
00:26:56,210 --> 00:26:57,420
辛苦啦
Now, our forensics

367
00:26:57,450 --> 00:27:00,500
辛苦啦
mustn't be tainted by any of the work that's gone before.

368
00:27:00,520 --> 00:27:03,980
辛苦啦
Previous investigations had all their testing done in-house

369
00:27:04,000 --> 00:27:05,900
辛苦啦
by the Forensic Science Service.

370
00:27:05,930 --> 00:27:08,080
辛苦啦
But the science has moved on.

371
00:27:08,130 --> 00:27:10,340
辛苦啦
We need a fresh pair of eyes on this.

372
00:27:10,360 --> 00:27:11,490
辛苦啦
Angela Gallop.

373
00:27:13,130 --> 00:27:14,660
辛苦啦
She has been involved in

374
00:27:14,690 --> 00:27:16,900
辛苦啦
some of the highest profile cases of the last ten years.

375
00:27:16,930 --> 00:27:20,930
辛苦啦
Lynette White, Stephen Lawrence, Damilola Taylor.

376
00:27:20,970 --> 00:27:23,140
辛苦啦
Dr Gallop and her team are the best in the business.

377
00:27:23,170 --> 00:27:25,020
辛苦啦
But they can only find what they're looking for

378
00:27:25,050 --> 00:27:27,500
辛苦啦
if they look in the right place. And that's where we come in.

379
00:27:27,530 --> 00:27:29,380
辛苦啦
We need to identify which items of evidence

380
00:27:29,410 --> 00:27:33,840
辛苦啦
are most likely to carry Cooper and/or victim DNA in whatever form.

381
00:27:33,890 --> 00:27:36,450
辛苦啦
Skin, hair, saliva, semen, blood.

382
00:27:36,490 --> 00:27:38,260
辛苦啦
Now, in an ideal world, there'd be no limit

383
00:27:38,280 --> 00:27:40,460
辛苦啦
to the amount of exhibits we could send for analysis.

384
00:27:40,490 --> 00:27:41,970
辛苦啦
But...

385
00:27:42,000 --> 00:27:43,460
辛苦啦
forensic work is not cheap.

386
00:27:43,490 --> 00:27:46,280
辛苦啦
And our budget is finite.

387
00:27:46,320 --> 00:27:48,690
辛苦啦
In short, whatever we send

388
00:27:48,730 --> 00:27:51,460
辛苦啦
needs to be chosen very fucking carefully.

389
00:27:56,560 --> 00:27:58,060
辛苦啦
Our first case tonight

390
00:27:58,080 --> 00:28:00,700
辛苦啦
is an extraordinary double murder in South Wales.

391
00:28:00,730 --> 00:28:03,210
辛苦啦
On the evening of 22nd December, 1985,

392
00:28:03,250 --> 00:28:05,820
辛苦啦
Richard Thomas and his sister, Helen Thomas,

393
00:28:05,840 --> 00:28:07,620
辛苦啦
were attacked in their home

394
00:28:07,650 --> 00:28:09,620
辛苦啦
at Scoveston Park, three miles outside Milford.

395
00:28:09,650 --> 00:28:11,420
辛苦啦
She was shot, probably in her bedroom.

396
00:28:11,450 --> 00:28:13,460
辛苦啦
And it was in that room at about ten o'clock

397
00:28:13,490 --> 00:28:15,140
辛苦啦
that the fire was started.

398
00:28:15,170 --> 00:28:18,820
辛苦啦
Richard Thomas died of shotgun wounds to the stomach and the head.

399
00:28:18,840 --> 00:28:23,250
辛苦啦
Emergency services were called at 1:15am on 23rd of December.

400
00:28:23,280 --> 00:28:26,300
辛苦啦
Scene of Crime Officers entered the property the following morning

401
00:28:26,320 --> 00:28:27,820
辛苦啦
and found Helen Thomas' body on a bed.

402
00:28:27,840 --> 00:28:29,620
辛苦啦
It's believed she was sexually assaulted.

403
00:28:29,650 --> 00:28:32,130
辛苦啦
On the morning of June 29th, 1989,

404
00:28:32,170 --> 00:28:36,760
辛苦啦
Peter and Gwenda Dixon were murdered on the Pembrokeshire Coastal Path

405
00:28:36,800 --> 00:28:38,060
辛苦啦
near Little Haven.

406
00:28:38,080 --> 00:28:41,100
辛苦啦
The couple from Oxford decided to take a short walk

407
00:28:41,130 --> 00:28:43,300
辛苦啦
while they waited for their tent to dry.

408
00:28:43,320 --> 00:28:46,460
辛苦啦
Their bodies were found six days later on the cliffs at Little Haven.

409
00:28:46,490 --> 00:28:50,000
辛苦啦
Now, one of Wales most spectacular beauty spots...

410
00:28:50,040 --> 00:28:55,520
辛苦啦
Between 7:45pm and 8:45pm on Wednesday 6th March, 1996,

411
00:28:55,560 --> 00:29:00,520
辛苦啦
five children, aged between 15 and 16, were attacked in a field

412
00:29:00,560 --> 00:29:01,900
辛苦啦
next to the Norton Hill Estate.

413
00:29:01,930 --> 00:29:04,890
辛苦啦
On the evening of November 22nd, 1996,

414
00:29:04,930 --> 00:29:08,840
辛苦啦
a bungalow in Sardis, six miles from Milford, was burgled.

415
00:29:08,890 --> 00:29:12,600
辛苦啦
The victim was confronted by a man in a balaclava.

416
00:29:12,650 --> 00:29:14,140
辛苦啦
They were approached by a masked man.

417
00:29:14,170 --> 00:29:16,420
辛苦啦
The children were threatened, told to lie on the ground.

418
